TextChange: , but most people aren't like that

On the spectrum from materialistic to utilitarian, most of us fall somewhere in the middle.  Most of our purchases are utilitarian, in that they serve a function and we'll shop for the best deal we can.  We don't all buy the best television or run to the grocery store in Jimmy Choo shoes, but we do splurge.  A woman may really want a great designer purse and will shell out $350 for one, but she may also own 3-4 others that came from Khols.  Should she be maligned because she cherishes that Michael Khors that she picked up?  Absolutely not!
